# Context Routing Map ([PROJECT_NAME])

Read when: always at session start.
Skip when: never.

Purpose: which docs to load beyond the startup set, and when.

## Default
Start with only `AI_AGENT.md`, `docs/SESSION_BRIEF.md`, `docs/CONTEXT_ROUTING.md`. Pull deeper docs only on the triggers below.

## Doc Triggers (Topic-Based)

| Doc | Load when |
|---|---|
| `docs/PROJECT_CANVAS.md` | milestone, scope, sequencing, or next action is unclear |
| `docs/ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK.md` | commands, tests, CI, validation, or feature execution rules matter |
| `docs/TECH_STACK.md` | architecture, dependency, or integration boundary decisions |
| `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` | entrypoint, route, function chain, side-effect, or smoke evidence changes (Tier B/C) |
| `docs/OPS_SECURITY_RELEASE.md` | deploy, secrets, auth, logging, data handling, or release path changes |
| `CHANGELOG.md` | documenting a behavior change or checking recent history |
| `AI_CONTEXT.md` | nearby code reads are insufficient and a generated map exists |
| `docs/AI_MEMORY.md` | recurring preferences or prior lessons matter |
| `docs/QUICKSTART_5_MIN.md` | first-time setup of this project |
| `docs/TEMPLATE_ADOPTION_WALKTHROUGH.md` | first install OR retrofitting templates-v2 into an existing project OR something feels "missing" / AI keeps ignoring a script that exists |

## Event Triggers (Action-Based)

These fire when the AI is *about to do* a specific kind of action. Same purpose as Doc Triggers, but keyed off an event in the work, not a topic in the user's question. Populated during adoption per `docs/TEMPLATE_ADOPTION_WALKTHROUGH.md` §2–§6.

| Event | Load / Run |
|---|---|
| About to bump or compare versions, OR versions look out of sync, OR about to release | `scripts/bump_version.sh` (run; never hand-edit version strings in individual files) |
| About to merge to `main` | `scripts/predeploy_full_suite.sh` and `docs/POST_CODING_CHECKS.md` |
| Behavior change without doc update suspected | `scripts/enforce_doc_updates.sh` |
| Template pack version bump | `scripts/check_template_drift.sh` and `docs/UPGRADE_GUIDE.md` |
| About to add or change a CI job | `.github/workflows/ci.yml` and `docs/ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK.md` |
| CI red after the worker reported DONE | `docs/POST_CODING_CHECKS.md` (the orchestrator review missed something) |
| About to add a new entrypoint or workflow | `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` and `docs/WORKFLOW_TEST_MATRIX.md` |
| About to add a new smoke test | `docs/SMOKE_TEST_CATALOG.md` |
| BUGFIX packet in flight | `docs/ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK.md` §3e regression accretion rule |
| Test file modified | `docs/POST_CODING_CHECKS.md` §3 test-honesty spot-check |
| Issuing a worker packet | `docs/WORKER_TASK_PACKET.md` |
| Worker returned DONE | `docs/POST_CODING_CHECKS.md` (mandatory review) |
| Worker returned BLOCKED twice on the same Path ID | `docs/INVESTIGATOR_PROTOCOL.md` |
| About to run unattended overnight | `AI_AGENT.md` § Unattended Run Rules |

If an event is not listed here and the AI is unsure, surface to user; do not improvise.

## Skip Rules
- Skip `CHANGELOG.md` for routine implementation unless documenting the change.
- Skip `OPS_SECURITY_RELEASE.md` for local UI or isolated test work.
- Skip `MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` for non-entrypoint edits in Tier A.
- Skip `TECH_STACK.md` when the task is local and architecture is already clear.

## Escalation
If more than three deeper docs seem necessary before the first edit, stop and ask whether the task is too broad or under-specified.
